User: In the figure below, a 3-inch by 3-inch square adjoins a 10-inch by 10-inch square. What is the area of the shaded region? Express your answer in square inches as a common fraction. [asy]
unitsize(2mm);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7pt)+fontsize(12pt));

pair H=(0,0), A=(0,10), B=(10,10), C=(10,3), G=(10,0), E=(13,3), F=(13,0);
pair D=extension(A,F,B,G);

draw(A--B--G--H--cycle);
fill(D--C--E--F--cycle, black);
draw(A--F);
draw(G--F--E--C);

label("$A$",A,NW);
label("$H$",H,SW);
label("$B$",B,NE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$G$",G,S);
label("$D$",D,WSW);
label("$E$",E,NE);
label("$F$",F,SE);
[/asy]
Assistant: <think>

solution:
Geometrically, $|z + 5 - 3i|$ is the distance between the complex numbers $z$ and $-5 + 3i$ in the complex plane, and $|z - 7 + 2i|$ is the distance between $z$ and $7 - 2i.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, Z;

A = (-5,3);
B = (7,-2);
Z = (6,6);

draw(A--B);
draw(A--Z--B);

dot("$-5 + 3i$", A, NW);
dot("$7 - 2i$", B, SE);
dot("$z$", Z, NE);
[/asy]

By the Triangle Inequality, the sum of the distances is minimized when $z$ lies on the line segment connecting the two complex numbers $-5 + 3i$ and $7- 2i,$ in which case the sum of the distances is simply $|(5 - 3i) - (-7 + 2i)| = |12 - 5i| = \boxed{13}.$

